      "email",
      {
        "html": "<p>When Silicon Valley Bank (SVB) scored approval for a major merger in 2021, it promised to deliver billions in loans to low-income communities as part of the deal. But when the government bailed out SVB’s wealthy depositors and rewarded its new corporate owner after the bank’s sudden collapse, federal regulators dispensed with that community benefit agreement — leaving thousands of affordable housing units and small-business endeavors in jeopardy. <a href=\"__GHOST_URL__/regulators-stiffed-low-income-communities-in-silicon-valley-bank-bailout/?utm_source=newsletter-email&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=newsletter-article\">Today’s featured story</a> by Rebecca Burns has the details below.</p><p><strong>Also:</strong></p><p>・The new season of <em>The Audit </em>podcast has launched. Hosts Dave Anthony and Josh Olson take a big leap into the astounding world of PragerU, a right-wing propaganda machine that aspires to become a force in American education. <a href=\"https://the.levernews.com/audit/\">Click here to listen to the first episode and learn more</a>.</p>"
      }
